    <!-- HELP -->
    <string name="help_title">Help &amp; guide</string>
    <string name="help_getting_started_title">Getting started</string>
    <string name="help_getting_started_content">1. Set the start date.\n2. Choose the first cycle day.\n3. Configure skip rules and labels.\n4. Save your changes.\n5. Add the widget to your home screen.</string>
    <string name="help_calculation_title">How cycle calculation works</string>
    <string name="help_calculation_content">The selected start date is the reference point for the cycle. The first cycle day is the label assigned to that date. The cycle advances only on included days. Skipped weekends and holidays do not move the cycle forward.</string>
    <string name="help_presets_title">Presets</string>
    <string name="help_presets_content">Presets fill the cycle fields with ready-made values. If you later edit the cycle manually, the preset changes to Custom.</string>
    <string name="help_widget_title">Widget</string>
    <string name="help_widget_content">You can add the widget from your launcher’s widget picker. The widget updates automatically and uses the saved app settings. Widget style affects appearance only.</string>
    <string name="help_faq_title">FAQ</string>
    <string name="help_faq_content">Why does the cycle not change on some days?\nBecause weekends or holidays may be skipped.\n\nWhy is the widget different from the app?\nCheck saved settings and widget style.\n\nWhy are notifications not working?\nMake sure notifications are enabled and permission is granted.</string>

